niu
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a pole erected for the religious ceremonial purposes of the 19th century Pai Marire cult. [Maori niu, divination] -->esp. in collocation with POLE, MAST
Origin:Maori
Register: historical

Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
